Software Sustainability Evaluation Pipeline - Requirements

Hardware
- CPU: 4+ cores recommended (git mining and Sonar scans are CPU-heavy).
- Memory: 8 GB minimum, 16 GB recommended for larger repos.
- Storage: 5-20 GB free depending on number/size of cloned repos and outputs.

Operating system
- Windows 10/11, macOS 12+, or Linux (Ubuntu 20.04+ recommended).

Software dependencies
- Python 3.10+.
- Git (for cloning repositories).
- SonarQube server (local or remote) and sonar-scanner on PATH.
  - Optional: run SonarQube via Docker if preferred.
- LLM provider access (local server or hosted endpoint).

Python packages
- See requirements.txt for pinned/compatible versions.

Network requirements
- Outbound HTTPS for cloning repositories and calling LLM/Sonar APIs.

Notes
- For reproducibility, record the repo HEAD SHA and analysis timestamp in outputs.
